  <regnum>358/2006</regnum>
  <change regulation="">
    <changenote eff="February 1, 2010">Regulation BEFORE repealed by BC Reg <amendingreg>321/2009</amendingreg>, effective February 1, 2010.</changenote>
    <reg index="">
      <regnum>358/2006</regnum>
      <oic>M268/2006</oic>
      <deposited>December 14, 2006</deposited>
      <acttitle>Local Government Act</acttitle>
      <title>Geotechnical Slope Stability (Seismic) Regulation</title>
      <content>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Definition</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>1</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>In this regulation, <term>building</term> has the same meaning as in the British Columbia Building Code.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Seismic parameters</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>2</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Where the intended use of land is the construction of a building, the geotechnical study and geohazard assessment for slope stability of that land must be based on ground motion values having a 10% probability of exceedance in 50 years.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 323, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 692]</provisionsnote>
      </content>
    </reg>
  </change>
